# 5. Create Dictionary from Two Lists

## Problem

Create a dictionary using keys and values.

### Example

```python
keys = ["name","age"]
values = ["Ram",25]
```

---

## Built-in Solution

```python
keys = ["name","age"]
values = ["Ram",25]

result = dict(zip(keys, values))

print(result)
```

### Output

```python
{'name':'Ram','age':25}
```

---

## Pure Logic Solution

```python
keys = ["name","age"]
values = ["Ram",25]

result = {}

for i in range(len(keys)):

    result[keys[i]] = values[i]

print(result)
```

